22:48.268 --> 22:50.270
We're all broken in need of grace.

22:50.711 --> 22:53.334
There's not one less sinful or more sinful.

22:53.394 --> 22:55.016
We are all under sin.

22:55.056 --> 22:56.517
Sin is sin.

22:56.557 --> 23:02.924
In God's eyes, no matter what it is, it's the same level of ungodliness.

23:03.685 --> 23:05.968
There's not extremes of ungodliness.

23:06.048 --> 23:08.050
There's either godly or not.

23:08.514 --> 23:10.236
And God is quite clear.

23:10.296 --> 23:13.600
There is no level of ungodliness.

23:13.901 --> 23:27.598
And so when we think about that, and when you think about that, it's a lot harder to look at someone and go, I can't believe you did that unless you say, well, I can't believe I did this at the same time.

23:28.579 --> 23:33.485
Can't believe you did that, but I can believe that I might have done that when I was younger.

23:33.525 --> 23:37.330
Those kind of conversations can actually open up people.

23:37.954 --> 23:42.078
to feel safe.

23:42.098 --> 23:50.906
The reason why is because people who sin that we know about and understand and the reputation precedes them, they need forgiven.

23:53.048 --> 23:56.231
Bottom line, they need forgiven and they need to know they are.

23:56.632 --> 24:02.477
They need to know that they can change and they're not condemned to that life for eternity or for the rest of this life.

24:02.998 --> 24:07.602
They need to know that grace is bigger than what they did, that the cross went deeper.

24:08.450 --> 24:16.983
Forgiveness keeps the house open to new people, to the people who are in there, and it keeps the relationship safe.

24:17.503 --> 24:21.569
Ephesians 4.32 says, forgive as Christ forgave.

24:24.714 --> 24:28.460
Offences and misunderstandings are going to happen.

24:30.162 --> 24:32.265
We aren't going to get out of this world without them.

24:32.305 --> 24:38.194
The question is whether we're going to forgive quickly and deeply.

24:38.946 --> 24:39.827
as Christ did.

24:42.509 --> 24:48.495
A safe place doesn't mean that there's nothing that's painful there or that nothing hurts.

24:50.057 --> 24:53.480
It means there's a healing culture for all wounds.

24:56.863 --> 24:59.786
We can be broken and loved.

25:00.847 --> 25:01.968
That's when you feel safe.

25:03.370 --> 25:07.794
And that's not always a culture in many places in this world.

25:10.562 --> 25:13.525
And when we feel safe, it creates staying power.

25:13.566 --> 25:18.311
When you feel welcomed and wanted and loved and accepted, you want to be there.

25:19.252 --> 25:32.488
Colossians chapter three, verses 12 through 15 says in part, put on tender mercies, kindness, humility, meekness, long suffering, forgiveness, and above all, love.

25:34.069 --> 25:38.034
People grow where they feel safe enough to be real.

25:39.362 --> 25:43.908
where they can be themselves and not go, here I am.

25:43.928 --> 25:45.110
Is that okay?

25:46.773 --> 25:50.578
Because once you feel like you can't be you, you don't feel safe.

25:53.662 --> 26:07.602
When compassion and humility become a normal part of a culture or atmosphere, people will stop performing, putting on masks and start being transformed by grace.

26:08.802 --> 26:13.867
because there's no need to pretend, or false pretense, people can be who they are.

26:15.869 --> 26:24.777
A reconciled church becomes a reconciliation witness in St. Corinthians chapter 5, verses 18 and 19.

26:24.857 --> 26:27.480
God gave us the ministry of reconciliation.

26:29.041 --> 26:34.686
The safe church isn't just comfortable, it's credible to the work of God.

26:35.988 --> 26:38.450
God is at work in the church here.

26:38.690 --> 26:50.728
We see that, we see answers to prayer, we see miracles, we see God doing things and it gives us confidence to bring more to the throne, to share more, to love more, to do more.

26:51.770 --> 27:03.788
When the atmosphere is there and it's protected and cherished unity in the church is visible to other people, they see how the people love each other.

27:05.611 --> 27:07.954
They see that they forgive each other quickly.

27:08.034 --> 27:10.557
that it's a normal part of their culture.

27:11.217 --> 27:14.621
It's not something you have to go, well, I don't know if I should or shouldn't.

27:15.021 --> 27:18.244
We understand this is what we do because we belong to Jesus.

27:18.845 --> 27:22.248
And humility in a church is attractive.

27:24.290 --> 27:25.171
It's beautiful.

27:26.432 --> 27:27.774
We're here because of grace.

27:29.035 --> 27:35.922
Not we're here because we belong to God and we're privileged.

27:37.282 --> 28:06.226
When humility comes grace that is talked about becomes believable and becomes accessible See the gospel isn't just a message It becomes an ecosystem And the guiding force is grace Our stories That we tell are not about what other people should be doing or fixing in their lives

28:06.946 --> 28:13.696
They're about what God redeemed us from and saved us to do and what we're trying to do to help others.

28:14.617 --> 28:17.522
That's the story of a healthy church and the people in it.

28:18.003 --> 28:20.727
We'll talk about whether people ought to be doing or changing.

28:21.207 --> 28:24.052
We talk about what God did for us when he's doing it through us.

28:25.854 --> 28:36.370
That's powerful because there's a lot of people who need to hear that we're about doing what God asks us to do, not about trying to get other people to fix themselves.

28:37.410 --> 28:38.191
We hear to love.

28:39.453 --> 28:46.523
And so I suggest that we use the safe filter when we share or speak to others.

28:47.825 --> 28:50.589
In other words, before you speak, run it through safe.

28:51.210 --> 28:59.161
And safe is an acrostic for the simple way of understanding what our speech needs to be seasoned with.

28:59.281 --> 29:03.407
As it says on here, season with salt and always with grace, this helps.

29:03.968 --> 29:05.650
Yes, it's got to be scriptural.

29:06.690 --> 29:07.812
It's gotta be accurate.

29:07.872 --> 29:10.936
Don't twist it to mean something else.

29:11.657 --> 29:15.962
It has to be faith building and it has to be edifying.

29:16.563 --> 29:22.331
If it doesn't pass that criteria, it's probably not worth saying and it's probably not safe.

29:24.634 --> 29:27.418
If it fails that criteria, don't say it.

29:27.458 --> 29:30.322
This isn't censorship either.

29:30.342 --> 29:33.586
This is just common sense discipleship and loving people.

29:34.786 --> 29:35.687
So how do we do this?

29:35.707 --> 29:37.689
